    "text": "<p>A Framework document rather than an architecture document, because multiple architectures are able to provide solutions. Selective disclosure is one kind of many other Zero-knowledge Proofs.</p>\n<p>It is necessary to support Protocols (in addition to data structures). Unfortunately protocols are not in the scope currently.</p>\n<p>Saying that JWT or CWT should be used to support is premature. As an example, a  JWT mandates that a claim should only be present once, whereas some attribute should be able to be present multiple times, e.g., \"age_Over\" = \"18\" and \"age_Over\" = \"15\" or \"Nationality\"= \"US\" and \"Nationality\" = \"CA\".</p>",
